The Death of “Death Taxes” in New Jersey




										06/23/2017 
										 | by Scott Miller, Jr.

On October 14, 2016, Governor Chris Christie enacted a new law that will dramatically change the role of “death taxes” in New Jersey. “Death taxes” refer to estate and inheritance tax, which are incurred by heirs following the death of a relative. New Jersey, along with Maryland, are the only two states that levy both…  Read more »
     




