Blue Bell Private Wealth Management Lifted By $1.92 Million Its Tri Continental (TY) Holding; Blue Martini Software Has 1.29 Sentiment

July 24, 2017 - By Ellis Scott

bluebird bio, Inc. is a clinical-stage biotechnology company. The company has market cap of $4.31 billion. The Firm is focused on developing gene therapies for severe diseases and cancer. It currently has negative earnings. With its lentiviral gene therapy and gene editing capabilities, it has built an integrated product platform with various applications in these areas.
Blue Bell Private Wealth Management Llc increased Tri Continental Corp (TY) stake by 16.53% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Blue Bell Private Wealth Management Llc acquired 87,281 shares as Tri Continental Corp (TY)’s stock rose 2.25%. The Blue Bell Private Wealth Management Llc holds 615,204 shares with $13.57 million value, up from 527,923 last quarter. Tri Continental Corp now has $1.40 billion valuation. It closed at $24.78 lastly. It is down 18.43% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 1.73% the S&P500.







Since March 22, 2017, it had 1 buying transaction, and 0 selling transactions for $228,628 activity. KING DAVID L bought $228,628 worth of Tri-Continental Corporation (NYSE:TY) on Wednesday, March 22.
Blue Bell Private Wealth Management Llc decreased Call Spy Mar17 @ 201 stake by 321 shares to 10 valued at $25,000 in 2016Q4. It also reduced Spdr S&P 500 Etf (SPY) stake by 5,473 shares and now owns 136,616 shares. Guggenheim Enhanced Eqty (GPM) was reduced too. 
Investors sentiment decreased to 1.52 in Q4 2016. Its down 0.06, from 1.58 in 2016Q3. It dropped, as 4 investors sold TY shares while 17 reduced holdings. 13 funds opened positions while 19 raised stakes. 7.56 million shares or 8.74% less from 8.28 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. 1832 Asset Mngmt Ltd Partnership invested in 0.01% or 120,000 shares. Oakworth Incorporated invested in 0.01% or 1,255 shares. Raymond James Financial holds 43,313 shares or 0.01% of its portfolio. Sei Invs reported 1,062 shares or 0% of all its holdings. Glenmede Tru Na, Pennsylvania-based fund reported 31 shares. Northern Corporation has invested 0% in Tri-Continental Corporation (NYSE:TY). Winslow Evans And Crocker reported 4,926 shares stake. Thomas J Herzfeld Advisors holds 222,821 shares or 2.27% of its portfolio. Signature Fincl Mgmt owns 0.71% invested in Tri-Continental Corporation (NYSE:TY) for 86,114 shares. 9,142 were reported by Stifel Fin Corp. Rmb Cap Mngmt Llc invested in 0.08% or 63,998 shares. Lazard Asset Mngmt Ltd Company owns 0.02% invested in Tri-Continental Corporation (NYSE:TY) for 501,675 shares. Zuckerman Grp Limited Liability invested 0.21% of its portfolio in Tri-Continental Corporation (NYSE:TY). Guggenheim Llc invested in 65,351 shares or 0% of the stock. Yorktown Rech Company Inc has 0.53% invested in Tri-Continental Corporation (NYSE:TY) for 95,000 shares.
Eventide Asset Management Llc holds 2.36% of its portfolio in bluebird bio Inc for 587,677 shares. First Light Asset Management Llc owns 71,246 shares or 1.93% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Deerfield Management Co has 0.77% invested in the company for 302,027 shares. The New York-based Armistice Capital Llc has invested 0.58% in the stock. Artal Group S.A., a Luxembourg-based fund reported 422,536 shares.
Analysts await bluebird bio Inc (NASDAQ:BLUE) to report earnings on August, 2. They expect $-1.63 earnings per share, down 2.52% or $0.04 from last year’s $-1.59 per share. After $-1.68 actual earnings per share reported by bluebird bio Inc for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -2.98% EPS growth. 
Ratings analysis reveals 50% of Bluebirdbio’s analysts are positive. Out of 4 Wall Street analysts rating Bluebirdbio, 2 give it “Buy”, 1 “Sell” rating, while 1 recommend “Hold”. The lowest target is $80.0 while the high is $87.0. The stock’s average target of $83.50 is -13.07% below today’s ($96.05) share price. BLUE was included in 4 notes of analysts from October 14, 2016. Leerink Swann maintained the stock with “Outperform” rating in Friday, October 14 report. The stock of bluebird bio Inc (NASDAQ:BLUE) earned “Sell” rating by Cantor Fitzgerald on Friday, October 14. The company was maintained on Thursday, December 1 by Maxim Group. Roth Capital downgraded bluebird bio Inc (NASDAQ:BLUE) on Monday, February 6 to “Neutral” rating.


